WEBVTT

00:00.120 --> 00:01.476
Previously on "Nashville"...

00:01.521 --> 00:04.312
That light was so bright,
it was like relief.

00:04.390 --> 00:05.806
I hate being this.

00:05.824 --> 00:08.642
Deacon Claybourne live at The Bluebird.

00:08.660 --> 00:09.943
I didn't mean to fall asleep.

00:09.978 --> 00:11.279
You want to take one of these?

00:11.313 --> 00:13.114
It's just like drinking
a few cups of coffee.

00:13.148 --> 00:15.266
Lamar Wyatt thought that
I was your star witness,

00:15.300 --> 00:16.417
but Tandy is.

00:16.452 --> 00:18.086
I'd rather see my father go free

00:18.120 --> 00:20.421
than to spend the rest of my
life looking over my shoulder.

00:20.456 --> 00:24.542
In a stunning turn of events,
Lamar Wyatt will be released.

00:24.593 --> 00:27.995
I realized that there is
one thing that I need... you.

00:30.182 --> 00:32.665
Ah, where is that thing?

00:32.683 --> 00:35.887
It's on your side.

00:40.025 --> 00:43.010
10 missed calls from Emily

00:43.028 --> 00:45.813
and an urgent text from your publicist.

00:45.847 --> 00:48.116
"Country-music titans
express outrage over"...

00:48.150 --> 00:49.784
just s... screw them.

00:49.818 --> 00:52.954
The world's made a sport
out of hating me, and I'm...

00:52.988 --> 00:55.123
I'm done with it.

00:55.157 --> 00:57.858
I'm just gonna stay off the grid.

00:57.876 --> 00:59.193
Right.

01:02.364 --> 01:04.331
Don't get it.

01:04.366 --> 01:06.834
- Don't get it.
- Juliette, it's my house.

01:06.868 --> 01:09.370
I'm getting the door.

01:11.206 --> 01:13.040
Hey!

01:13.058 --> 01:15.376
- I'm not here!
- Okay.

01:15.394 --> 01:17.512
Mr. Barkley.

01:17.546 --> 01:19.180
Deacon.

01:19.214 --> 01:21.516
You got a minute?

01:21.550 --> 01:24.352
Sure, hey, what's up?

01:24.386 --> 01:26.687
Well, uh, I was gonna
record my set tomorrow night

01:26.721 --> 01:28.889
for my "Live at The Bluebird" E.P.

01:28.907 --> 01:30.691
- Great idea.
- Well, thank you. I just...

01:30.725 --> 01:33.528
Erika tells me that Gunnar's, uh, quit,

01:33.562 --> 01:35.780
so he's not working on the
board anymore, but you are.

01:35.831 --> 01:37.198
- Is that right?
- Yep.

01:37.232 --> 01:39.116
Well, look, you know my
sound. You know my music.

01:39.168 --> 01:40.334
I was thinking...

01:40.369 --> 01:42.703
why don't you just engineer
this whole thing for me?

01:42.737 --> 01:44.622
- Seriously?
- Yeah.

01:44.673 --> 01:46.624
I'd love to.

01:46.675 --> 01:47.875
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

01:47.909 --> 01:49.260
All right, all right, well,
I got a shoestring budget,

01:49.294 --> 01:51.179
but I got a little bit of
money I can throw at you.

01:51.213 --> 01:52.680
I just...

01:52.714 --> 01:54.782
I want this thing to sound like
we're really at The Bluebird.

01:56.084 --> 01:59.153
Yeah, I hear you, and, hey  you know what?

01:59.188 --> 02:01.339
We could record the whole thing on analog,

02:01.373 --> 02:03.374
you know, record it live to two-track.

02:03.408 --> 02:05.676
Yes, yes, yes, all that. That's great.

02:05.727 --> 02:06.944
Great, so, uh,

02:06.979 --> 02:09.396
how about I meet up with
you later for a dry run?

02:09.431 --> 02:10.481
Okay.

02:12.651 --> 02:13.801
Hey.

02:15.521 --> 02:16.904
You been in touch with Juliette?

02:16.939 --> 02:18.839
- Uh, she's all right.
- Yeah?

02:18.874 --> 02:21.893
Yeah, just laying low, you
know, keeping her head down.

02:21.927 --> 02:24.562
She sure stirred up a hornet's
nest with that Opry performance.

02:24.596 --> 02:26.597
She's a hardheaded little
damn thing, isn't she?

02:26.648 --> 02:28.866
- All right, man, I'll talk to you later.
- Yeah, see you.

02:33.822 --> 02:36.457
♪ Well, you know how it
goes when you meet somebody ♪

02:36.491 --> 02:39.043
♪ that you like somebody,
wanna hold somebody ♪

02:39.094 --> 02:41.546
♪ but you just can't stand
to think about somebody ♪

02:41.597 --> 02:46.968
♪ as another somebody
becoming someone else ♪

02:47.002 --> 02:52.139
♪ when it all goes to hell ♪

02:52.173 --> 02:56.861
♪ why can't we keep
it on the sweet side? ♪

02:56.895 --> 03:03.150
♪ See how it feels
to take a slow ride ♪

03:03.184 --> 03:05.536
♪ this time ♪

03:05.571 --> 03:07.738
Cut! Got that piece... moving on.

03:07.789 --> 03:09.206
Good job, y'all.

03:09.241 --> 03:11.208
- Rayna, we got about 20 minutes till our next setup.
- Okay.

03:14.429 --> 03:15.930
- Looking great.
- Thanks, Robbie.

03:15.964 --> 03:17.198
- Hi!
- Hi.

03:17.232 --> 03:19.116
Why didn't you tell me you were flying in?

03:19.167 --> 03:20.635
I wanted to hop on a plane

03:20.669 --> 03:22.219
and see how the shooting was going.

03:22.254 --> 03:23.387
It's going.

03:23.422 --> 03:25.072
It's costing us a lot of money.

03:25.107 --> 03:26.841
Well, it has to. It's like you said.

03:26.875 --> 03:29.576
The first single off the label,
it's got to make a big splash.

03:29.595 --> 03:31.845
- Yeah. Fingers crossed.
- Yes.

03:31.863 --> 03:33.814
How are you? I missed you.

03:33.832 --> 03:35.466
The girls really missed you.

03:35.500 --> 03:37.134
- Mm.
- How was the spa?

03:37.185 --> 03:38.536
It was really nice.

03:38.570 --> 03:39.853
How's Luke?

03:39.871 --> 03:41.188
- He's good. He's good.
- Yeah?

03:41.206 --> 03:43.457
Yeah, he's, uh, back out
on tour for another week,

03:43.491 --> 03:44.909
which is probably a blessing.

03:44.943 --> 03:47.011
- Why?
- Since daddy's getting released.

03:48.213 --> 03:49.730
You know, I still don't understand

03:49.765 --> 03:51.082
what happened with all that.

03:51.116 --> 03:54.468
But then I figure, maybe
he's actually innocent.

03:54.503 --> 03:56.837
Wouldn't that be a pleasant surprise?

03:56.872 --> 03:59.357
Oh, my gosh, of course, the
girls are planning a big,

03:59.391 --> 04:01.676
you know, welcome-home
party for him this afternoon.

04:01.710 --> 04:03.494
This afternoon? Oh, sweetie,

04:03.528 --> 04:05.096
I can't. I have meetings. I have so many.

04:05.147 --> 04:07.698
No, no, no, don't you dare. Listen to me.

04:07.733 --> 04:10.751
I don't know what went
down between the two of you,

04:10.753 --> 04:13.270
but our father is coming home from prison.

04:13.322 --> 04:15.239
I'm not doing that by myself.

04:15.273 --> 04:16.974
We are gonna be a family, damn it.

04:17.024 --> 04:20.244
Good morning.

04:20.295 --> 04:21.562
Good morning!

04:21.596 --> 04:23.681
Oh. Hey.

04:23.732 --> 04:25.616
Hmm, what are you listening to?

04:25.667 --> 04:27.001
Demos.

04:27.035 --> 04:30.421
Edgehill sent over like 30
songs they want me to listen to.

04:30.472 --> 04:33.240
- Anything good?
- Not really.

04:33.275 --> 04:35.943
Apparently, my album drops May 1st.

04:35.977 --> 04:38.195
Against Rayna Jaymes' album.

04:38.263 --> 04:40.314
Hey, but that's a compliment, right?

04:40.348 --> 04:42.299
Label thinks you can take her on.

04:42.334 --> 04:43.684
Well, not with these demos, I can't.

04:43.719 --> 04:44.852
That's the problem with having

04:44.886 --> 04:46.404
a great song like "What if I was willin'?"

04:46.438 --> 04:48.489
It makes all these
others pale in comparison.

04:48.523 --> 04:51.759
Well, you know...

04:51.793 --> 04:53.661
seeing as you're looking...

04:53.695 --> 04:54.995
Huh?

04:55.029 --> 04:58.699
I wrote it after the whole Brent thing.

04:58.734 --> 05:02.253
"I've always been broken
underneath my smile.

05:02.287 --> 05:05.106
If I'm being honest, I
didn't stand a chance."

05:05.140 --> 05:07.458
Yeah, look, you got to have
more than just up-tempo stuff

05:07.492 --> 05:08.976
to round out the album, you know?

05:09.010 --> 05:11.945
Have a ballad in there. I'm not broken.

05:11.963 --> 05:13.731
And this isn't my brand.

05:14.733 --> 05:16.701
Dude, this is me you're talking to.

05:16.752 --> 05:19.203
Remember?

05:19.237 --> 05:21.572
Hey, you look nice.
Where, uh, where you going?

05:21.623 --> 05:23.974
Oh, I'm just headed out... errands.

05:24.009 --> 05:26.744
Okay, your hair looks
nice and different and...

05:26.795 --> 05:28.596
Thanks.

05:28.630 --> 05:30.097
O... okay.

05:32.801 --> 05:35.786
- Am I crazy, or was that weird?
- Yes.

05:35.821 --> 05:37.521
To both.

05:38.907 --> 05:41.108
The band's just playing
the hell out of the songs.

05:41.126 --> 05:43.294
I'll tell you something
about Avery Barkley, too.

05:43.345 --> 05:45.379
Boy knows what he's doing. Just perfect.

05:45.413 --> 05:47.281
You know, it's just such a great way

05:47.315 --> 05:49.834
to ease back into this craziness.

05:49.885 --> 05:52.420
It's just a little E.P.
at The Bluebird, you know?

05:52.454 --> 05:54.021
Well, that's great.

05:54.055 --> 05:56.390
Yeah, your enthusiasm...
it's really contagious.

05:56.408 --> 05:58.893
I just can't believe
they let Lamar Wyatt walk.

05:58.927 --> 06:00.294
Yeah, I can.

06:00.328 --> 06:02.813
This case got you all
wrapped up, doesn't it?

06:02.848 --> 06:04.782
Legal system's got so many loopholes

06:04.816 --> 06:07.001
that the law can't keep up with it anymore.

06:07.035 --> 06:08.903
I love when you talk dirty like that.

06:08.937 --> 06:10.871
- Oh, yeah?
- Yeah.

06:10.906 --> 06:13.174
You are gonna rock a
recording at The Bluebird.

06:14.609 --> 06:15.810
How's that for enthusiasm?

06:15.844 --> 06:18.129
It's really good enthusiasm.
I want some more of it.

06:18.180 --> 06:19.847
Mm, sorry. Got to be at work.

06:21.266 --> 06:23.334
And I'm sorry I don't know
how late I'm gonna be tonight.

06:23.368 --> 06:24.702
Yeah, well, that's all right for tonight,

06:24.753 --> 06:26.286
but you got to promise to
be there tomorrow night.

06:26.304 --> 06:27.621
Oh, I will be there...

06:27.639 --> 06:29.623
in the front row enthusiastically.

06:29.641 --> 06:30.624
Hi.

06:30.693 --> 06:32.244
Hi, Scarlett. Bye, Scarlett.

06:32.295 --> 06:34.346
- Bye. Hello.
- Hey.

06:34.381 --> 06:36.999
I figured you moved out
and decided not to tell me.

06:37.017 --> 06:39.268
No, I, uh, I laid down
three more tracks with Liam.

06:39.302 --> 06:40.820
It was like my best vocals ever.

06:40.871 --> 06:42.221
- Really?
- Yeah.

06:42.255 --> 06:44.323
Uh, what does Megan
have front-row seats for?

06:44.357 --> 06:45.574
Should I be jealous?

06:45.642 --> 06:47.626
No, it's just my recording at The Bluebird.

06:47.661 --> 06:48.994
I know you're busy with Liam, so...

06:49.045 --> 06:51.213
No, no, he's... he's got to
go someplace with some people.

06:51.248 --> 06:52.748
Uh, I got Rayna's music video tomorrow,

06:52.766 --> 06:54.784
and then I'm coming to The Bluebird.

06:54.818 --> 06:57.319
Okay, busy girl, just make
sure you get some rest.

06:57.354 --> 06:59.321
I can't. I got songs pouring out of me.

06:59.356 --> 07:00.840
I got to keep up with them.

07:04.928 --> 07:06.562
Hi, everyone.

07:06.580 --> 07:08.364
You'll be asked about your
training and experience.

07:08.398 --> 07:11.467
And be sure to list any touring
and studio experience you have.

07:11.501 --> 07:13.152
Sophia Roxanne?

07:15.572 --> 07:17.656
Thanks.

07:17.691 --> 07:20.726
And, uh, Zoey Dalton.

07:20.777 --> 07:23.145
Just need your head shot and demo.

07:23.163 --> 07:26.665
Oh, um, I don't have those.

07:26.700 --> 07:28.784
Have you ever worked as
a backup singer before?

07:30.804 --> 07:33.038
Well, honey, come back when
you got your tools ready.

07:34.908 --> 07:37.693
Right.

07:39.162 --> 07:41.864
I'm just saying you might
want to prepare yourself.

07:41.898 --> 07:43.565
Why? Does he look that bad?

07:43.583 --> 07:45.668
Well, you know, he's lost weight.

07:45.702 --> 07:47.219
He looks frail.

07:47.254 --> 07:49.822
I mean, the man's been
locked up, for God sakes,

07:49.856 --> 07:52.024
and he had a heart
attack before that, so...

07:52.058 --> 07:53.659
Well, he's not the man he used to be.

07:53.710 --> 07:54.776
He's here!

07:54.795 --> 07:56.612
All right, well, now
y'all don't smother him.

07:56.630 --> 07:58.347
Just... just don't bounce off the walls.

07:58.381 --> 07:59.515
We can hug him, right?

07:59.549 --> 08:01.317
Yeah, of course you can hug him.

08:07.007 --> 08:08.057
Grandpa!

08:08.091 --> 08:09.375
Hello, ladies.

08:09.426 --> 08:11.026
Mm!

08:11.061 --> 08:13.162
Mm! Pa-paw.

08:13.196 --> 08:17.232
- Hi, daddy.
- Oh, I missed you.

08:17.250 --> 08:18.701
Hey.

08:18.735 --> 08:20.419
- How you doing, Tandy?
- Hi, daddy.

08:20.453 --> 08:22.037
Haven't seen hide nor hair of you

08:22.071 --> 08:23.506
since your one and only visit.

08:23.540 --> 08:25.424
I know. I'm sorry. I've just been so busy.

08:25.458 --> 08:27.760
Well, why don't we get inside
where it's nice and warm?

08:27.794 --> 08:29.929
Oh, shoot, you know, I have to run.

08:29.963 --> 08:32.464
I got a million things to do,
and you probably want to rest.

08:32.515 --> 08:34.133
You're not gonna stay for a bite?

08:34.183 --> 08:35.551
Well, you want your company up and running,

08:35.585 --> 08:37.019
and we'll have dinner
this week or something.

08:37.020 --> 08:38.304
Hey, hey.

08:38.355 --> 08:40.972
You said you were gonna stay for this.

08:41.024 --> 08:42.942
I'm sorry. I can't.

