♪ looks like it's gonna
be a beautiful day ♪

09:04.274 --> 09:08.544
♪ children outside laugh as they play ♪

09:08.578 --> 09:12.231
♪ just listen to that
little bluebird sing ♪

09:12.249 --> 09:16.836
♪ you never know what
the day's gonna bring ♪

09:16.870 --> 09:21.090
♪ the sun is shining ♪

09:21.124 --> 09:24.960
♪ the sun is shining down ♪

09:25.011 --> 09:28.580
♪ there's a silver lining ♪

09:28.598 --> 09:33.252
♪ behind every cloud, they say ♪

09:33.270 --> 09:38.424
♪ looks like the
blues have blown away ♪

09:38.458 --> 09:45.097
♪ blown awa-y-y ♪

09:45.115 --> 09:48.267
That is the most beautiful
thing I've ever seen or heard.

09:48.285 --> 09:49.919
- Thank y'all.
- And we made you cookies.

09:49.953 --> 09:51.103
You did?

09:51.121 --> 09:52.771
We did.

09:52.789 --> 09:54.106
Well, I will have one.

09:54.124 --> 09:57.076
And, um, how about a big old glass of milk?

09:57.110 --> 09:58.127
Okay.

09:58.161 --> 10:01.764
They have been practicing like crazy.

10:01.798 --> 10:04.116
I don't know why they'd have
to. They got your talent.

10:04.134 --> 10:06.285
Unlike your sister.

10:06.303 --> 10:09.288
You know, she... she never
once looked me in the eye today.

10:09.322 --> 10:11.507
Well, listen, I think it's gonna take

10:11.541 --> 10:13.676
a little time for all of us to heal.

10:17.597 --> 10:19.481
Wait. You're leaving?

10:19.516 --> 10:21.433
Yeah, got to go wrangle the equipment

10:21.484 --> 10:23.269
for Deacon's show at The Bluebird.

10:23.303 --> 10:25.437
I made toast.

10:26.940 --> 10:31.076
Uh, that's not toast.
That's, uh, lukewarm bread.

10:31.111 --> 10:34.096
I had to microwave it. I
couldn't find your toaster.

10:34.130 --> 10:35.981
That's 'cause I don't have a toaster.

10:38.151 --> 10:43.122
You sure I can't entice you into
staying a little while longer?

10:43.156 --> 10:46.375
I'll watch that weird
Sci-Fi movie with you.

10:46.426 --> 10:49.378
It's Fellini, not Sci-Fi.

10:49.429 --> 10:52.381
And do you really want
me to piss Deacon off?

10:52.432 --> 10:54.266
Yes.

10:54.301 --> 10:55.601
No.

10:55.635 --> 10:57.636
- No?
- No.

10:57.670 --> 10:59.638
See you soon.

11:04.561 --> 11:06.111
You know, Layla,

11:06.146 --> 11:07.496
you don't have to buy
groceries for the house.

11:07.530 --> 11:09.014
I have to contribute
something around here hello.

11:09.032 --> 11:10.282
- 'Cause you won't let me pay any money.
- Hey, we're in here.

11:10.317 --> 11:11.700
Think fast.

11:11.735 --> 11:12.785
Oh! Whoop!

11:12.819 --> 11:15.871
- How was errand running?
- Fine.

11:15.906 --> 11:17.039
Hey.

11:17.073 --> 11:18.407
Hi.

11:18.458 --> 11:20.075
It's kind of a full house, right?

11:20.126 --> 11:22.378
Well, I can take care
of that. I got to split.

11:22.412 --> 11:25.214
Laying down some vocals
on my boy Gunnar's track.

11:25.248 --> 11:27.216
- Meet me at the studio?
- I'll see you there in a while.

11:27.250 --> 11:28.467
Hey, I haven't gotten to tell you, uh,

11:28.501 --> 11:29.668
"American Hitmaker" called.

11:29.702 --> 11:31.804
They're flying me to L.A. tomorrow

11:31.838 --> 11:33.806
to debut my next single
on the top-10 show.

11:33.840 --> 11:35.874
- Oh, that's great.
- Yeah, congratulations.

11:35.892 --> 11:37.643
Yeah, that's awesome.

11:37.677 --> 11:38.877
What, no kiss?

11:38.895 --> 11:40.379
I'm going to L.A.

11:40.397 --> 11:41.680
Walk me out.

11:41.714 --> 11:43.148
I got to split.

11:43.183 --> 11:45.651
I'm gonna swing by music row
before meeting up with Will.

11:45.685 --> 11:47.403
You got anything exciting happening?

11:47.437 --> 11:48.904
Just work.

11:48.939 --> 11:50.572
Okay, well, have fun with that.

11:50.607 --> 11:52.992
Mwah. See you later.

11:58.949 --> 12:00.399
Avery.

12:00.417 --> 12:02.584
I have to find Juliette.

12:02.619 --> 12:04.586
Everything is blowing up.
She's completely M.I.A.

12:04.621 --> 12:06.088
Do you have any idea where she is?

12:07.540 --> 12:09.191
- I haven't seen her.
- Really?

12:14.180 --> 12:17.499
Great, well, thanks for your help.

12:19.786 --> 12:21.520
Well, I know putting Scarlett in

12:21.554 --> 12:23.388
is gonna cost us a little bit more,

12:23.406 --> 12:24.990
but I do think it's... oh.

12:25.024 --> 12:26.175
Uh, hey, buck, can I call you right back?

12:26.209 --> 12:27.309
Call you right back. Bye.

12:27.344 --> 12:28.610
Hey.

12:28.701 --> 12:30.468
Is there anybody else here? I
mean, are the girls home yet?

12:30.503 --> 12:32.153
Uh, no. What's going on?

12:32.188 --> 12:34.205
I thought there were security concerns.

12:34.240 --> 12:35.490
Yeah, listen.

12:35.508 --> 12:38.326
There's something you really
need to know about your father

12:38.360 --> 12:40.028
before you get too close to him.

12:40.062 --> 12:41.996
Lamar's responsible for Peggy's death.

12:42.031 --> 12:44.599
- What?
- You see, he targeted me

12:44.633 --> 12:47.368
because he thought I was
cooperating with the prosecution.

12:47.402 --> 12:51.222
He thought that I turned him in,
that I was their star witness,

12:51.273 --> 12:53.241
so he ordered that man to shoot me,

12:53.275 --> 12:55.794
and instead my wife died
for nothing because...

12:55.828 --> 12:57.045
- Hold on...
- It wasn't me.

12:57.079 --> 12:58.463
I didn't know enough about Lamar's business

12:58.497 --> 13:00.148
to tip off the feds, much
less talk to them about it,

13:00.182 --> 13:01.483
but she did.

13:01.517 --> 13:03.068
- Who? I don't know what you're t...
- So I don't want...

13:03.102 --> 13:05.052
I don't want our girls
anywhere near either of them.

13:05.071 --> 13:06.554
- Okay, okay, okay, okay, okay, hold on!
- You understand?

13:06.605 --> 13:08.156
I know you're grieving

13:08.190 --> 13:11.326
and... and you're trying to
make sense of all this, but I...

13:11.360 --> 13:12.994
I mean, this sounds crazy.

13:13.028 --> 13:15.864
Ask your sister why she didn't
testify on Lamar's behalf.

13:15.898 --> 13:18.533
Ask her what your father is capable of

13:18.567 --> 13:20.251
because she knows better than anybody.

13:25.546 --> 13:28.281
♪ baby, baby, baby-y-y ♪

13:28.315 --> 13:31.951
♪ what if you wanted to feel alive? ♪

13:31.986 --> 13:35.255
♪ Make something of the
time you're killin' ♪

13:35.289 --> 13:39.709
- ♪ what if you wanted somebody to love you right? ♪
- It's not bad.

13:39.727 --> 13:41.027
Yeah, I'm not sold on the bridge.

13:41.061 --> 13:42.795
- ♪ What if I... ♪
- Could we give it another pass?

13:42.830 --> 13:44.580
Hold up. Let me check your mike.

13:44.615 --> 13:47.149
Think you're too hot.

13:48.469 --> 13:49.686
Thinks you're too hot.

13:49.720 --> 13:53.256
- Right?
- Hey, guys.

13:53.290 --> 13:54.524
How's the session going?

13:54.558 --> 13:55.672
Fine.

13:55.676 --> 13:58.828
Jeff sent me over. He wants to
know your thoughts on the demos.

13:58.863 --> 14:00.630
Gotta start locking down
tracks for the album.

14:00.664 --> 14:03.416
Yeah, I'm not really feeling
anything in that batch.

14:03.450 --> 14:06.202
Come on, Will, some of
those songs are great.

14:06.253 --> 14:07.837
Yeah, well, I don't like 'em.

14:07.888 --> 14:10.456
And I'm the one singing
them, so keep looking.

14:10.491 --> 14:14.127
Okay. We'll send over some more songs.

14:14.161 --> 14:16.412
Mm.

14:16.447 --> 14:18.448
You know, you're kidding yourself

14:18.482 --> 14:20.666
if you think you got
this thing under control.

14:20.684 --> 14:24.270
I'm telling you, man,
anybody in a 10-foot radius

14:24.305 --> 14:26.138
can tell there's something
going on between you two.

14:40.487 --> 14:42.521
I know you're here, Juliette.

14:48.228 --> 14:50.396
How many calls do I not have to answer

14:50.431 --> 14:51.881
before you get the message?

14:51.932 --> 14:53.533
How did you know I was here?

14:53.567 --> 14:56.402
Avery's a terrible liar.
Why are you ignoring me?

14:56.437 --> 14:58.605
Because I'm quitting everything.

14:58.639 --> 15:00.690
Before everyone quits you.

15:00.724 --> 15:01.941
I guess you figured out

15:01.976 --> 15:04.344
that country radio is dumping
you from their playlist.

15:04.378 --> 15:07.680
Stop talking! I don't
know. I don't want to know.

15:07.715 --> 15:09.265
This is my life now.

15:09.300 --> 15:11.651
What? It's a nice apartment.

15:12.993 --> 15:14.194
If you need references,

15:14.228 --> 15:16.346
I'll call and talk to whoever you want.

15:16.380 --> 15:18.281
I am not looking for another job.

15:18.315 --> 15:20.183
I work for you.

15:20.217 --> 15:21.851
Let me take you home. No.

15:24.371 --> 15:26.839
But you can help me with something.

15:29.844 --> 15:33.246
Oh, I see why you had to
leave daddy's in such a hurry.

15:33.264 --> 15:34.864
You had to go get a haircut.

15:34.899 --> 15:37.116
Among other things.

15:37.134 --> 15:39.169
Looks nice.

15:39.203 --> 15:40.687
Thanks.

15:40.721 --> 15:42.622
I filed our letters of incorporation.

15:42.656 --> 15:46.092
I got all our bank accounts
set. You just need to sign these.

15:48.145 --> 15:50.413
Teddy came by here a little while ago.

15:50.464 --> 15:53.316
- How's he doing?
- Not good.

15:53.367 --> 15:56.302
He had some real strange
things to say about you.

15:56.337 --> 15:57.854
Really?

15:57.888 --> 16:01.107
He says you're responsible
for daddy's prosecution.

16:02.776 --> 16:04.076
Are you?

16:06.430 --> 16:08.348
They'd already set their sights on him.

16:08.382 --> 16:10.166
I just provided a little information.

16:10.217 --> 16:11.501
So, suddenly it's so important to you

16:11.552 --> 16:12.902
to have our father arrested for fraud?

16:12.937 --> 16:14.520
- I...
- What, did they have something on you?

16:14.538 --> 16:17.056
I wanted him punished.

16:17.091 --> 16:18.942
Why?

16:20.160 --> 16:22.078
He's responsible for mom's death.

16:22.112 --> 16:24.914
It wasn't an accident. He ran
her off the road that night.

16:24.949 --> 16:27.500
- He was in Louisville that night.
- No, he wasn't.

16:27.534 --> 16:29.919
How do you know?

16:29.954 --> 16:34.173
I found out right before he was arrested.

16:34.208 --> 16:35.842
You found out and you didn't tell me?

16:35.876 --> 16:37.510
The U.S. attorney approached me,

16:37.528 --> 16:39.329
and I was forbidden from telling you.

16:39.380 --> 16:41.464
Everybody in this family is a damn liar!

16:41.498 --> 16:43.483
No, I'm sor...

16:45.386 --> 16:49.756
♪ I know when to walk
away when the fists fly ♪

16:49.790 --> 16:52.775
♪ I never had a problem with goodbye ♪

16:52.810 --> 16:56.045
♪ and I know right from wrong ♪

16:56.096 --> 16:58.147
Hey, Jeff, come on in.

16:58.198 --> 16:59.649
Hey.

16:59.700 --> 17:01.467
Thank you for coming down here.

17:01.501 --> 17:03.536
Yeah. You said it was important.

17:03.570 --> 17:05.954
I... I don't even know how to put this.

17:05.990 --> 17:07.640
Hey, hey. Tell me what's going on.

17:08.826 --> 17:12.979
I don't think, uh, me
and Brent are connecting.

17:13.012 --> 17:16.132
I mean, he doesn't see me

17:16.165 --> 17:18.300
for who I am or who I want to be.

17:18.335 --> 17:21.320
Was he inappropriate in any way?

17:21.355 --> 17:24.173
Well, it makes me uncomfortable.

17:24.208 --> 17:25.791
Right.

17:25.826 --> 17:27.727
And, I mean, on top of that,

17:27.761 --> 17:30.262
he's picking all the wrong demos for me.

17:30.281 --> 17:33.099
There's got to be somebody
else you can throw on my team.

17:36.870 --> 17:42.158
Listen, will, you are a massive
part of Edgehill's future.

17:42.192 --> 17:44.327
I will look after you personally,

17:44.378 --> 17:46.412
and I'll take care of Brent, okay?

17:46.447 --> 17:47.997
Thank you. I appreciate it.

17:48.032 --> 17:49.966
Absolutely.

17:50.000 --> 17:51.567
Hey, now... now focus.

17:51.602 --> 17:53.152
Focus on finding songs.

17:53.170 --> 17:55.271
May 1st will be here before we know it.

18:01.178 --> 18:02.795
Hey.

18:02.830 --> 18:04.547
I'm gonna move back to my house.

18:04.598 --> 18:06.182
If that's what you want to do.

18:09.803 --> 18:11.821
Listen, after the U.S. attorney told me

18:11.872 --> 18:14.573
that daddy may have something
to do with mom's death,

18:14.591 --> 18:17.910
I hired a private
investigator to look into it.

18:19.129 --> 18:21.280
That's the report.

18:23.167 --> 18:25.034
I'm not lying now.

18:27.954 --> 18:29.672
Whole damn thing's surreal.

18:29.707 --> 18:31.007
I mean, Lamar's at home

18:31.041 --> 18:33.459
probably drinking his third scotch by now,

18:33.494 --> 18:35.028
gloating as he always does.

18:35.062 --> 18:36.612
I don't think this is over yet.

18:36.647 --> 18:39.182
What do you mean? He's untouchable.

18:40.851 --> 18:42.435
Federal agents contacted me,

18:42.469 --> 18:44.420
wanting details about Stoffel's case.

18:44.455 --> 18:46.439
They think there's some validity

18:46.473 --> 18:48.674
to your theory that Lamar's involved.

18:48.709 --> 18:49.942
It's more than a theory.

18:49.977 --> 18:51.494
I know. That's why they're
digging for evidence.

18:51.528 --> 18:53.463
'Cause if they can't find
evidence of corruption,

18:53.497 --> 18:55.714
how the hell are they gonna
prove that he ordered a hit?

18:55.733 --> 18:58.401
Peggy deserves better.

18:58.435 --> 18:59.769
I know.

18:59.820 --> 19:01.838
Don't lose hope.

19:03.824 --> 19:05.007
Hey.

19:06.460 --> 19:07.994
What the hell's going on here?

19:08.028 --> 19:10.046
- What, are you his lawyer now, too?!
- No, I'm not.

19:10.097 --> 19:11.347
Okay, look, Deacon, just calm down.

19:11.382 --> 19:12.782
- We're friends, okay?
- You're friends?

19:12.833 --> 19:14.016
- Yeah.
- Yes, let me explain.

19:14.051 --> 19:15.668
- I... I should go.
- Yeah, you should go.

19:15.702 --> 19:17.587
Thank you for the information.

19:17.621 --> 19:19.188
Of course. I'll let you
know what I find out.

19:25.095 --> 19:26.896
What you gonna let him know?

19:26.930 --> 19:29.882
That is privileged information.

19:29.917 --> 19:31.434
The kind that requires y'all to hold hands?

19:31.468 --> 19:34.003
He is upset about his wife's death.

19:35.355 --> 19:37.407
He's a part of this big case
that I've been working on.

19:37.458 --> 19:40.293
Wait. He's the big...

19:40.327 --> 19:42.095
he's the reason you've been staying out

19:42.129 --> 19:43.513
all these hours late at night?!

19:43.564 --> 19:45.998
Yes, I have been helping him, yes.

19:46.033 --> 19:48.551
'Cause I understand
what he's going through.

19:48.585 --> 19:50.503
Are you some kind of, like...

19:50.570 --> 19:52.422
tragedy junkie or something?

19:52.456 --> 19:53.923
- Is that what it is?
- Excuse me?

19:53.957 --> 19:55.741
No, no, that's it, right?
That's why you're with me.

19:55.759 --> 19:57.076
I'm this hot-headed alkie

19:57.094 --> 19:59.879
that you, uh, seduced to
fulfill your savior complex.

19:59.913 --> 20:01.297
What... what are you talking about?!

20:01.348 --> 20:03.749
I'm talking about you latching
on to people that got problems

20:03.767 --> 20:05.384
so you can feel better about yourself!

20:05.418 --> 20:06.636
That's what I'm talking about!

20:06.670 --> 20:08.938
You can leave now.

20:08.972 --> 20:10.640
You're right. I can.

20:10.691 --> 20:12.225
I will.

20:17.510 --> 20:20.946
♪ People say and, honey, people do ♪

20:21.013 --> 20:25.650
♪ and there's a difference
between the two ♪

20:25.718 --> 20:30.556
♪ we know what's right
and we know what is wrong ♪

20:30.623 --> 20:35.026
♪ but it all runs
together before too long ♪

20:35.094 --> 20:37.495
I didn't cook it, but I ordered it.

20:37.563 --> 20:39.698
What the hell have you
done to my apartment?

20:41.505 --> 20:44.158
I don't need you to buy me things.

20:44.226 --> 20:46.210
It's a... couch and a bed.

20:46.362 --> 20:48.663
Yeah, and a table and foofy pillows.

20:48.731 --> 20:51.332
I mean, I liked my old couch.

20:51.400 --> 20:53.602
Those pillows are unisex!

20:53.669 --> 20:56.004
Okay, okay. Hey, hey, hey,
hey, listen, listen, listen.

20:57.573 --> 21:00.021
I totally understand
the instinct to hide out,

21:00.089 --> 21:02.290
but you can't be afraid of those people.

21:02.357 --> 21:04.260
I'm not afraid of them.

21:05.787 --> 21:07.226
I just feel like...

21:08.984 --> 21:10.804
All I have left is you.

21:10.924 --> 21:14.371
You are the only one who
can change the conversation,

21:14.491 --> 21:17.224
and you sure as hell can't
do that cooped up in here.

21:20.027 --> 21:21.897
There is no conversation.

21:37.745 --> 21:38.896
So, look, the bottom line is

21:38.921 --> 21:40.692
we've just lost two of
our top-grossing artists,

21:40.729 --> 21:42.963
and so the pressure is on
to keep our artists happy

21:43.083 --> 21:44.596
and to launch the next generation.

21:44.809 --> 21:47.518
Agreed. So, what do you need from me?

21:49.902 --> 21:51.184
We need to cut you loose.

21:52.749 --> 21:53.743
What?

21:54.044 --> 21:57.103
The talent is not comfortable around you.

21:58.673 --> 22:01.283
I've been nothing but professional.

22:01.308 --> 22:02.859
You'll receive a good severance

22:02.884 --> 22:04.923
- after you sign a nondisclosure.
- Five years

22:05.043 --> 22:07.302
and... and leaving my
life in L.A., and this is

22:07.371 --> 22:08.937
- what I get?
- It's not personal.

22:08.987 --> 22:10.995
It's business. I have
to protect my artists.

22:11.189 --> 22:12.328
I'm sorry, man.

22:28.291 --> 22:29.898
Crap, oh, crap, crap!

22:29.929 --> 22:32.595
One of the other partners is
taking over the Stoffel case.

22:32.607 --> 22:34.509
I can't do it anymore.

22:34.629 --> 22:36.505
It's because of Deacon, isn't it?

22:36.530 --> 22:38.185
Because it's unprofessional.

22:38.253 --> 22:41.221
Deacon is connected to
Maddie and the Wyatt family.

22:41.289 --> 22:42.724
I thought I could manage,

22:42.749 --> 22:45.151
but the demands of the case
have become too much for me.

22:45.176 --> 22:47.235
I just want you to know that

22:47.355 --> 22:48.730
I feel like you're the only person

22:48.755 --> 22:50.795
I can really talk to about all of this.

22:51.098 --> 22:52.422
You know?

22:53.135 --> 22:54.825
Well, you'll find someone else.

22:55.936 --> 22:58.354
You just have to be open to it.

23:04.898 --> 23:06.994
- Oh, hey, Brent. Come in.
- Hey, man.

23:07.588 --> 23:09.140
Hey, you riding to the airport with me?

23:09.172 --> 23:10.786
No. Um,

23:10.906 --> 23:12.988
- Jeff just fired me.
- Wait. What?

23:13.251 --> 23:14.340
Why?

23:14.402 --> 23:16.542
He says I'm not a good fit.

23:17.975 --> 23:19.727
Man, I'm sorry to hear that.

23:19.775 --> 23:21.960
That... that's crazy.
I'm gonna call him, okay?

23:21.992 --> 23:23.230
Will, we have to call Jeff, right?

23:23.249 --> 23:24.563
Uh, I think your car's here.

23:24.600 --> 23:25.789
I'll be fine.

23:26.778 --> 23:28.611
Knock 'em dead out in L.A.

23:30.525 --> 23:32.401
Thank you for everything.

23:32.427 --> 23:33.891
Okay, take care.

23:37.797 --> 23:40.392
Sorry to hear that, man. Really.

23:40.586 --> 23:41.663
Thanks.

23:44.472 --> 23:46.862
Well, I guess you got what you wanted.

23:47.356 --> 23:48.695
I don't know what you mean.

23:48.895 --> 23:50.315
I'm really good at my job.

23:50.435 --> 23:52.004
I'm gonna be more than okay.

23:52.124 --> 23:55.427
But you just lost your
biggest ally at Edgehill.

23:55.689 --> 23:58.286
I guess I'll have to look
after myself from now on.

23:58.711 --> 24:00.344
Good luck with that.

24:09.079 --> 24:11.475
So, you had him fired?

24:11.819 --> 24:13.665
I didn't mean to.

24:14.497 --> 24:16.668
I just didn't want him around me.

24:17.337 --> 24:19.702
You said yourself people
could tell there was a problem.

24:19.734 --> 24:22.042
So you think one guy is a problem?

24:22.162 --> 24:24.057
What, remove that guy,
and, hey, everything's cool!

24:24.079 --> 24:24.811
Yeah, exactly.

24:24.842 --> 24:26.281
Dude, you tried to kiss me!

24:29.615 --> 24:32.306
Look, I know things have been strange

24:32.506 --> 24:33.895
lately,  but it's over.

24:34.015 --> 24:35.290
I know what I want,

24:35.346 --> 24:37.499
and I'm not gonna let
anybody get in my way.

24:37.619 --> 24:40.264
Yeah. I can see that.

24:44.976 --> 24:46.064
Hey.

24:46.089 --> 24:47.453
Hey.

24:48.054 --> 24:49.718
A... are you feeling all right?

24:49.838 --> 24:51.896
Yeah, I'm fine. I just, uh...

24:52.016 --> 24:53.954
I've been working really
late nights on the album.

24:53.992 --> 24:56.488
- I'm good.
- Good, 'cause they need you at rehearsal.

24:56.520 --> 24:57.320
Okay.

24:57.389 --> 24:59.710
Uh, would you guys mind
giving me just a minute?

24:59.754 --> 25:00.837
Thank you.

25:01.019 --> 25:03.440
I'm not... wait. I'm not
holding Rayna up, am I?

25:03.465 --> 25:05.367
No, it's just your part today.

25:05.487 --> 25:07.144
She's at home with family.

25:23.870 --> 25:26.090
Not a lot of room on this couch

25:26.108 --> 25:27.685
with all these pillows.

25:28.824 --> 25:32.046
They're italiano. Like the movie.

25:33.310 --> 25:34.880
That's French.

25:35.121 --> 25:35.825
Hmm.

25:39.442 --> 25:40.461
All right.

25:41.199 --> 25:43.307
- You have to go?
- Yeah.

25:43.364 --> 25:45.679
Deacon's show is at
8:00, and I got to set up.

25:46.798 --> 25:48.200
Why don't you come with me?

25:48.807 --> 25:50.471
No thank you.

25:50.738 --> 25:53.286
Juliette, you're gonna
go stir-crazy in here.

25:53.937 --> 25:55.914
I got all your artsy-fartsy films

25:55.945 --> 25:57.816
that I don't understand
to get through. I'll be...

25:57.936 --> 25:58.948
Fine.

26:00.381 --> 26:01.939
All right, well...

26:02.164 --> 26:03.516
I'm gonna miss you.

26:07.552 --> 26:09.992
You know, just because
you close your eyes...

26:10.823 --> 26:12.624
Doesn't mean you're invisible.

26:33.925 --> 26:35.376
Hello, Rayna.

26:39.906 --> 26:42.040
Did you kill my mother?

26:43.735 --> 26:45.418
Your mother and I were
fighting about Watty.

26:46.645 --> 26:48.749
She came down with her bags packed.

26:50.323 --> 26:52.276
I figured she'd get about
halfway down the driveway

26:52.307 --> 26:53.896
and turn around.

26:55.918 --> 26:57.268
But she didn't.

26:58.696 --> 27:00.434
She meant it this time.

27:00.829 --> 27:03.388
I had to go after her.

27:05.233 --> 27:07.147
Beg her just to come back to me.

27:07.172 --> 27:09.180
I couldn't let her go, Rayna.

27:10.241 --> 27:12.421
I loved her too much to lose her.

27:12.966 --> 27:15.280
She must've seen me
in her rear-view mirror

27:15.305 --> 27:17.075
because she sped up, and...

27:17.488 --> 27:18.871
Of course, so did I.

27:18.927 --> 27:22.375
She was going so fast. She lost control.

27:22.495 --> 27:24.746
So you saw her crash.

27:25.922 --> 27:28.663
But you didn't get help.
You didn't do anything.

27:28.688 --> 27:30.565
Oh, I tried.

27:31.866 --> 27:35.927
I ran down to her car. She'd
gone over this embankment.

27:38.129 --> 27:40.663
But when I got there...

27:42.377 --> 27:44.711
There was nothing I could do.

27:46.294 --> 27:48.546
She was already...

27:49.385 --> 27:51.931
She was already gone.

27:54.534 --> 27:56.037
And then you just went off to Louisville

27:56.042 --> 27:57.149
and just lied about it.

27:57.193 --> 27:58.826
I just panicked.

28:00.503 --> 28:02.993
I left her there...

28:03.937 --> 28:07.203
Alone on the side of the r... road.

28:21.349 --> 28:22.913
Hey, what's going on with you?

28:23.257 --> 28:24.533
Nothing.

28:25.146 --> 28:26.316
Look, I'm...

28:26.436 --> 28:28.843
I'm sorry if I've been so busy lately.

28:28.887 --> 28:32.585
No, it's not you. I'm
just frustrated, I guess.

28:32.705 --> 28:33.873
About what?

28:34.706 --> 28:38.861
I mean, you, Scarlett, Avery, Will,

28:38.873 --> 28:41.300
you guys all have these awesome
things that you're doing,

28:41.343 --> 28:42.851
you know, and I don't.

28:43.252 --> 28:45.679
A year ago, I was sitting in Natchez,

28:45.799 --> 28:47.517
and I realized I had to get out of there

28:47.518 --> 28:49.808
because I didn't want to
be that girl who never left.

28:49.839 --> 28:52.942
But is sitting around
in Nashville any better?

28:52.980 --> 28:55.007
It's not like you're not doing anything.

28:55.407 --> 28:56.922
Gunnar, I'm a waitress.

28:56.947 --> 28:58.773
Well, and you're my girlfriend.

29:00.769 --> 29:03.178
Look, y... you're thinking
about this all wrong, okay?

29:03.298 --> 29:05.067
You did it. You got out of Natchez.

29:05.086 --> 29:06.156
And to the tune of working

29:06.187 --> 29:08.389
in one of country music's
most revered venues.

29:08.509 --> 29:10.047
You got a front-row seat.

29:10.504 --> 29:13.195
I don't think I want a
front-row seat anymore.

29:13.258 --> 29:14.828
Look...

29:14.948 --> 29:17.762
there are  hundreds of people

29:17.780 --> 29:20.771
who would kill to have your job, your life.

29:21.879 --> 29:24.757
But when you think it's
time for something new...

29:25.358 --> 29:27.022
I'll be there, okay?

29:27.460 --> 29:29.574
Hey, guys. Listen up a sec.

29:29.637 --> 29:31.633
