30:44.610 --> 30:47.094
No, I'm gonna do that when
I want and where I want.

30:47.313 --> 30:49.634
You were right about hiding out.

30:49.853 --> 30:53.143
Turns out I hate being invisible
more than I hate being wrong.

30:54.814 --> 30:55.621
Scarlett.

30:55.640 --> 30:56.928
- Hey.
- Hey.

30:57.191 --> 30:58.261
You look great.

30:58.267 --> 30:59.881
Oh, t... thank you. I feel great.

30:59.938 --> 31:01.333
It's really nice to see you guys.

31:01.370 --> 31:03.460
Um, enjoy the show. You look fantastic.

31:03.817 --> 31:05.332
That was friendly.

31:05.399 --> 31:07.321
And totally weird.

31:07.853 --> 31:09.602
Oh, wow, your hair!

31:10.193 --> 31:11.595
Uh, it's so glamorous.

31:11.632 --> 31:13.788
- Thank you.
- How are you?

31:13.908 --> 31:15.667
I'm okay. Good.

31:15.711 --> 31:17.770
Can I please have a Tequila and pineapple

31:17.820 --> 31:20.016
and, um, one of those
things of sweet potato fries?

31:20.066 --> 31:22.005
- Sure.
- Thank you.

31:26.222 --> 31:27.279
Hey.

31:27.573 --> 31:28.406
Hi.

31:30.095 --> 31:31.747
I didn't think you were gonna come.

31:31.809 --> 31:33.367
I didn't think you'd call.

31:33.755 --> 31:35.701
That was a nice message.

31:35.821 --> 31:38.078
I'm sorry. I just got
caught off guard there.

31:38.109 --> 31:39.842
No, you were right.

31:40.080 --> 31:42.658
I do like to save people.

31:42.778 --> 31:44.298
That's how we met.

31:44.823 --> 31:47.057
But it's not why I love you.

31:48.940 --> 31:50.705
Good evening, ladies and gentlemen,

31:50.730 --> 31:53.045
and welcome to a very special night

31:53.088 --> 31:54.990
at the Bluebird Café.

31:56.868 --> 31:58.007
I gave up the case,

31:58.038 --> 32:00.440
- so I won't be talking to Teddy anymore.
- You didn't have to do that.

32:00.472 --> 32:01.786
- I want more time for us.
- We're making a live recording.

32:01.906 --> 32:04.476
- Make an album.
- And I want to welcome our special guest tonight,

32:04.477 --> 32:06.297
our very own Deacon Claybourne.

32:06.360 --> 32:08.162
Thank you, Erika.

32:08.362 --> 32:10.239
Thank you, everybody.

32:10.487 --> 32:12.155
Most of y'all know my story.

32:12.448 --> 32:14.869
Had some, uh, rough patches along the road.

32:15.182 --> 32:16.947
Wasn't too long ago that in, uh,

32:16.978 --> 32:18.928
one of my darkest times,

32:18.995 --> 32:20.143
uh, an angel appeared.

32:20.187 --> 32:21.776
I'd like to do this first one for her.

32:29.159 --> 32:34.008
♪ Distance don't mean a thing ♪

32:36.222 --> 32:41.903
♪ I come when you pull the strings ♪

32:43.054 --> 32:46.539
♪ the strings of my heart ♪

32:46.608 --> 32:49.749
♪ wherever you are ♪

32:49.774 --> 32:55.230
♪ just pull, tug, tease ♪

32:56.731 --> 33:03.251
♪ time isn't all it seems ♪

33:03.371 --> 33:08.669
♪ no measure of you and me ♪

33:10.295 --> 33:14.312
♪ hours turn into days ♪

33:14.318 --> 33:17.327
♪ though I'm far away ♪

33:17.447 --> 33:23.064
♪ just pull, tug, tease ♪

33:23.133 --> 33:26.637
♪ I'll keep coming back ♪

33:27.243 --> 33:30.147
♪ oh, it's true ♪

33:30.197 --> 33:33.600
♪ I'll keep coming back ♪

33:33.720 --> 33:37.272
♪ that's what I do ♪

33:37.316 --> 33:40.732
♪ I retrace my tracks ♪

33:44.549 --> 33:47.152
♪ to you ♪

33:48.516 --> 33:49.686
There are a lot of things

33:49.717 --> 33:52.539
that I would've done
differently, should've done.

33:52.971 --> 33:54.723
But I acted out of love for your mother.

33:54.741 --> 33:56.237
You have to believe that.

33:56.531 --> 33:59.572
Yeah, I don't really know
what I believe anymore.

34:03.544 --> 34:05.139
I mean, you just...

34:05.208 --> 34:08.099
just lied about this... this whole time.

34:08.149 --> 34:09.601
And Tandy...

34:10.127 --> 34:11.315
Wait a minute. Is this...

34:11.435 --> 34:13.493
is this why she's so angry with me?

34:13.837 --> 34:16.101
I mean, does she blame me
now for your mother's death?

34:16.132 --> 34:17.929
Well, you were involved.

34:18.985 --> 34:21.120
I mean, maybe not
intentionally, but you were.

34:21.163 --> 34:22.420
Don't you think

34:22.541 --> 34:25.159
that I feel the guilt of
that every day of my life?

34:25.799 --> 34:28.772
Maybe this is a blessing
that it's out in the open.

34:28.891 --> 34:30.623
Maybe we can get past it now,

34:30.655 --> 34:32.257
the three of us, and find some peace.

34:32.288 --> 34:33.958
That's all I want now.

34:34.509 --> 34:36.092
That all you want now?

34:37.956 --> 34:40.259
'Cause you know what I
want? I want the truth.

34:42.237 --> 34:44.882
Did you have anything to
do with Peggy's murder?

34:45.409 --> 34:47.335
Why would you even ask such a thing?

34:47.367 --> 34:48.668
Did you think that

34:48.675 --> 34:51.346
Teddy was responsible for your prosecution?

34:51.553 --> 34:53.266
Oh, I have no doubt about that.

34:53.297 --> 34:55.168
Did you hire that man to shoot at Teddy?

34:55.206 --> 34:57.540
I didn't hire anyone to do anything.

34:57.596 --> 34:59.867
- I was in jail.
- Oh, I know you were in jail.

34:59.987 --> 35:01.500
Did you have somebody else do it for you?

35:01.525 --> 35:03.133
Did you have Albert do it for you?

35:03.253 --> 35:05.604
The shooter obviously had his own reasons

35:05.629 --> 35:07.875
- for hating Teddy.
- Dad, dad, did you do it?!

35:08.063 --> 35:09.620
He didn't need any prodding

35:09.639 --> 35:11.529
- from me or anyone else!
- You're not even denying this!

35:11.554 --> 35:12.868
What is it that you want me to do?

35:12.911 --> 35:15.620
I don't want you to deny it! I
want you to tell me the truth!

35:18.437 --> 35:21.764
Did you try to murder the
father of my children?!

35:28.281 --> 35:29.597
I don't want you near me.

35:29.615 --> 35:31.318
I don't want you near
my children ever again.

35:31.355 --> 35:33.808
As far as I'm concerned,
both of my parents are dead.

35:42.616 --> 35:47.421
♪ Starin' at my shadow
for way too long ♪

35:47.765 --> 35:52.914
♪ if I never did nothing,
then nothing could wrong ♪

35:53.089 --> 35:55.673
♪ I've always been singing ♪

35:55.692 --> 35:57.757
♪ I never had a song ♪

35:58.163 --> 36:00.453
♪ is that who I am? ♪

36:04.214 --> 36:07.816
♪ I see big, bright lights ♪

36:07.854 --> 36:12.308
♪ burning in the atmosphere ♪

36:14.154 --> 36:17.646
♪ callin' my name ♪

36:19.560 --> 36:22.326
♪ callin' my name ♪

36:25.361 --> 36:30.885
♪ sayin' I-I-I-I-I-I-I ♪

36:31.348 --> 36:37.021
♪ I don't have to be
the way I've been and ♪

36:37.141 --> 36:41.195
♪ I-I-I-I-I-I-I ♪

36:41.232 --> 36:47.220
♪ still got a lot of soul
underneath my skin and ♪

36:47.977 --> 36:53.382
♪ it's callin' my name ♪

36:53.720 --> 36:56.391
♪ callin' my name ♪

36:56.435 --> 36:59.150
♪ is that who I am? ♪

37:01.921 --> 37:03.836
Don't... don't stop, man.

37:03.956 --> 37:06.770
I mean, it's better than
I ever imagined it. It's...

37:07.559 --> 37:09.176
perfect for you.

37:10.718 --> 37:13.396
You're the only who's
ever gonna hear me sing it.

37:17.288 --> 37:20.235
- All right.
- Thank you. Thank you very much.

37:20.285 --> 37:22.218
Thanks. It was really nice to meet you.

37:22.274 --> 37:24.702
Oh, so good!

37:24.752 --> 37:27.073
- Yeah?
- So, so good.

37:28.068 --> 37:29.263
Yeah.

37:29.702 --> 37:32.386
- Think so?
- Oh, look at me. I'm a mess.

37:32.423 --> 37:33.712
You look good to me.

37:33.832 --> 37:36.190
- I'm gonna freshen up.
- All right.

37:39.300 --> 37:41.371
Well, looky here.

37:41.421 --> 37:42.679
Ah!

37:42.799 --> 37:44.512
That was an amazing show.

37:44.535 --> 37:46.569
To think I almost didn't come.

37:46.689 --> 37:48.596
Yeah, well, I'm so glad you did.

37:48.608 --> 37:51.149
Never want to stay too long
at a pity party, you know?

37:51.718 --> 37:53.164
A pity party's about the only invitation

37:53.195 --> 37:55.135
- I can get these days.
- Don't you let them

37:55.173 --> 37:56.155
get you.

37:56.180 --> 37:57.813
You've been given a voice, girl.

37:57.933 --> 37:59.164
You just keep saying what you believe,

37:59.183 --> 38:00.553
and you're gonna be fine.

38:00.572 --> 38:01.598
Hmm.

38:01.623 --> 38:02.912
Deacon, you killed it, man.

38:02.937 --> 38:04.126
- Oh, yeah?
- Oh, yeah!

38:04.151 --> 38:06.686
- We get it?
- You know, it's like pure bottled Bluebird.

38:06.723 --> 38:08.594
It's gonna sound great.

38:08.638 --> 38:10.728
That's all I wanted.

38:11.528 --> 38:13.312
So, is this a...

38:14.688 --> 38:16.496
I like it.

38:18.692 --> 38:20.193
Yeah.

38:23.684 --> 38:26.305
You know, I think we need
to get back in the studio.

38:26.324 --> 38:28.376
We wrote a great song.

38:28.420 --> 38:29.896
You're a hell of a producer.

38:29.909 --> 38:32.868
We... we need to do more of that.

38:33.162 --> 38:35.164
Oh, I think that's a fine idea.

38:35.451 --> 38:37.460
- Good.
- Just one thing.

38:37.580 --> 38:38.955
What?

38:39.387 --> 38:42.102
I want all my furniture back.

38:44.442 --> 38:46.169
Hey. Thank you.

38:46.225 --> 38:48.728
Hey, are you... okay?

38:48.848 --> 38:51.106
Yeah, I'm... great.

38:51.156 --> 38:53.671
I'm really happy. I'm
I'm busy as hell. I'm, uh,

38:53.791 --> 38:55.836
I'm recording, and I'm writing, and I'm...

38:55.880 --> 38:58.320
I'm doing press, and I've just taken
a break from the tour for the moment

38:58.338 --> 38:59.990
to keep recording the album.

39:00.021 --> 39:02.574
But I'll be back soon, and my
whole life's just kind of...

39:02.605 --> 39:03.844
perfect.

39:03.913 --> 39:06.453
Give my best to Gunnar. See ya.

39:14.418 --> 39:17.233
Thanks for coming. Well, look who's back.

39:18.046 --> 39:19.485
I don't have a demo.

39:19.535 --> 39:22.144
I don't have any professional experience.

39:22.176 --> 39:25.310
But this is a recording of my church solo.

39:25.654 --> 39:27.075
I can sing.

39:27.369 --> 39:29.508
I can really sing.

39:34.794 --> 39:35.996
Where's aunt Tandy?

39:36.014 --> 39:37.072
Her stuff's gone.

39:37.192 --> 39:39.393
Yeah, um, she left.

39:39.599 --> 39:40.963
Did you guys get in a fight?

39:41.144 --> 39:42.646
Is she coming back?

39:44.704 --> 39:47.174
Uh, come here.

39:48.933 --> 39:50.591
I think your aunt Tandy

39:50.616 --> 39:52.987
and your grandfather and
I are just gonna have to...

39:53.181 --> 39:56.704
Take a little... a little
time apart from each other.

40:04.261 --> 40:05.756
What are you doing here?

40:05.876 --> 40:07.351
Oh, I'm just trying to figure out

40:07.357 --> 40:09.440
why you're so hell-bent on destroying me,

40:09.472 --> 40:11.136
filling Rayna, the feds,

40:11.155 --> 40:13.070
anybody that'll listen to you full of lies.

40:13.101 --> 40:15.528
You got something to say to me, say it.

40:15.566 --> 40:17.618
The most powerful man in Nashville

40:17.738 --> 40:19.908
just assumed that he
was surrounded by people

40:19.946 --> 40:21.554
who would endlessly do his bidding.

40:21.610 --> 40:22.574
You never thought...

40:22.618 --> 40:24.163
- Never thought what, Teddy?!
- Never thought

40:24.213 --> 40:26.272
that the one who betrayed you

40:26.309 --> 40:27.561
was right under your nose!

40:27.611 --> 40:29.520
Is this more lies, Teddy?

40:29.570 --> 40:31.598
I couldn't have brought
you down if I wanted to.

40:31.718 --> 40:33.912
Only someone who stood by you

40:33.956 --> 40:36.121
and worked with you for 15 years

40:36.190 --> 40:38.349
and who knew where the bodies
were buried could do that...

40:38.380 --> 40:40.169
your own flesh and blood.

40:40.588 --> 40:42.484
Not Tandy.

40:42.909 --> 40:43.879
Because of you,

40:43.923 --> 40:46.732
my wife is buried in the
middle of Mount Olivet cemetery,

40:46.757 --> 40:47.658
and so help me God,

40:47.696 --> 40:49.529
I will make sure you pay for that one day.

40:56.593 --> 40:57.544
Lamar?

40:57.594 --> 40:59.183
Help me.

41:06.322 --> 41:07.542
Help me.

41:08.950 --> 41:10.151
Ple...

